dct_description_sm: Map of Sweden and Norway, pages 73 and 74 of the XXth Century Citizen's atlas--judging from state of various railways (such as Norway's Bergen & Arendal lines) and lack of the 1912 edition's third inset map, this was likely taken from an edition later than 1909, but earlier than 1912.
Relief shown by hachures and spot heights.
Bar scales in "British Statute Miles," "Swedish Miles," and "Norwegian Miles."
Shows railways (including projected), cities and towns, waterways.
